{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"4c0b22b6-923e-408f-805a-01d0f09752e8","content":"Here's what you need:\n\n**Environment variables** tell the .NET runtime to invoke `createdump` on crash, and **`SYS_PTRACE`** is required because `createdump` uses `ptrace` to snapshot the process.\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: v1\nkind: Pod\nspec:\n  containers:\n    - name: my-app\n      # ... your existing image, ports, etc.\n      env:\n        - name: DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump\n          value: \"1\"\n        - name: DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType\n          value: \"4\"                          # 1=Mini, 2=Heap, 3=Triage, 4=Full\n        - name: DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName\n          value: \"/tmp/dumps/coredump.%p.%t\"  # %p=PID, %t=timestamp\n        - name: DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath\n          value: \"/opt/tools/createdump\"      # required for NativeAOT (not bundled)\n      securityContext:\n        capabilities:\n          add: [\"SYS_PTRACE\"]                 # createdump needs ptrace access\n      volumeMounts:\n        - name: dump-volume\n          mountPath: /tmp/dumps\n  volumes:\n    - name: dump-volume\n      emptyDir:\n        sizeLimit: 2Gi                        # adjust based on expected dump size\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n- **`DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath`** — mandatory for NativeAOT since `createdump` isn't bundled with the published app.\n- **`MiniDumpType=4`** (Full) gives complete memory; use `2` (Heap) if size is a concern.\n- **`emptyDir`** works for transient collection; swap to a **PersistentVolumeClaim** if you need dumps to survive pod restarts.\n- Dump filenames include PID and timestamp to avoid collisions on repeated crashes.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"84c52fa3-f838-4477-ba0c-c63a83b66017","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to configure automatic crash dump collection for a NativeAOT .NET 11 app running in Kubernetes. They have `createdump` installed at `/opt/tools/createdump`.\n\nFor .NET NativeAOT crash dump collection, the key environment variables are:\n\n1. `DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump=1` - Enable mini dump collection on crash\n2. `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType` - Type of dump (1=Mini, 2=Heap, 3=Triage, 4=Full)\n3. `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName` - Path/pattern for dump files\n\n\n4. `DOTNET_CreateDumpDiagnostics` - Enable diagnostics for the createdump tool itself\n\nFor NativeAOT specifically, I need to set the core variables: `DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump=1`, choose an appropriate dump type with `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType`, and configure where the dumps should be written.\n\nNow I'm thinking through the Kubernetes configuration changes needed—I'll need a writable volume for the dumps, the environment variables set on the container, and potentially some security context adjustments like `SYS_PTRACE` capability since createdump requires elevated permissions to attach to processes.","outputTokens":1217},"id":"d66a0b58-9a7b-404e-aa9f-c254f6de0880","timestamp":"2026-04-03T00:58:40.041Z","parentId":"fc7a2d80-d251-4e83-87ae-0b1aacc2f887"}
